In a Cabinet meeting, President Trump celebrates the passage of the tax reform bill, calling it a "historic victory." He thanks Republican leaders and highlights key provisions of the bill, such as tax cuts for the middle class, a new family tax credit, and the lowering of the corporate tax rate. He also mentions the repeal of the individual mandate in the Affordable Care Act and the opening of the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge (ANWR) for oil drilling. The President emphasizes the positive impact of the tax cuts on the economy, job creation, and national security. He also calls for funding for the border wall, an end to chain migration and the visa lottery program, and stronger immigration enforcement. The Vice President and Cabinet members express their gratitude and support for the President's agenda.